---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - QuiKey">
    <section class="privacy-page">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="privacy-content">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2026</p>

                <p>
                    QuiKey is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle your data, with a focus on transparency and the protection of your personal information.
                </p>

                <section class="data-handling">
                    <h2>1. Data Accessed</h2>
                    <p>
                        To provide its core functionality, QuiKey accesses specific user data through third-party services you authorize.
                    </p>
                    <p><strong>Google User Data:</strong> QuiKey requests the following permissions (scopes):</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Send email on your behalf</strong> (<code>gmail.send</code>): Used to send files and messages as emails from your account.</li>
                        <li><strong>See and download your Google Drive files</strong> (<code>drive.file</code> and <code>drive.metadata.readonly</code>): Used to upload files to your Drive and list folders for destination selection.</li>
                        <li><strong>See your primary Google Account email address</strong> (<code>userinfo.email</code>): Used to identify your account and display which account is currently logged in.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Other Data:</strong> The app may access files on your local machine that you explicitly select to send or process.</p>

                    <h2>2. Data Usage</h2>
                    <p>We use the accessed data exclusively to perform actions initiated by you:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Composing and sending emails from your account.</li>
                        <li>Listing and searching for folders to help you select a file destination.</li>
                        <li>Uploading or saving files to your cloud storage.</li>
                        <li>Displaying your account email for session management within the app.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>We <strong>do not</strong> use this data for building advertising profiles, selling your information to third parties, or any purpose other than the specific tasks you perform in the app.</p>
                    <p><strong>Limited Use Disclosure:</strong> QuiKey's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs to any other app will adhere to <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.</p>

                    <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Local Security:</strong> All authentication tokens (including Google OAuth tokens), API keys, and session data are stored locally on your device in encrypted form.</li>
                        <li><strong>No Server Storage:</strong> We do not transmit or store your Google user data, email contents, or files on our own servers. All data transfer occurs directly between your device and the official APIs of the services you use.</li>
                        <li><strong>Application Logs:</strong> Diagnostic logs are stored locally and can be deleted by the user at any time.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
                    <p>We do not share your personal data with any third parties, except:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>With the <strong>service provider</strong> to fulfill the action you initiated (such as sending an email or uploading a file).</li>
                        <li>If explicitly directed by you (e.g., sending a file to a specific recipient).</li>
                        <li>With <strong>AI providers</strong> (like OpenAI or Anthropic) <strong>only if and when</strong> you explicitly use a feature that involves processing a file or text through those specific services. Only the selected content is transmitted.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>AI/ML Training Disclosure:</strong> Data obtained from Google APIs is never used to train generalized AI/ML models. We maintain strict data segregation between Google API services and third-party AI integrations.</p>
                </section>

                <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
                <p>QuiKey connects to these services based on your actions:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Google</strong> (Gmail, Drive, Gemini) — <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> (ChatGPT) — <a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> (Claude) — <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>OpenRouter</strong> (optional AI routing) — <a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>CloudConvert</strong> (optional PDF conversion fallback) — <a href="https://cloudconvert.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CloudConvert Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> (payments and licensing) — <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lemon Squeezy Privacy Policy</a></li>
                </ul>

                <h2>6. Optional Analytics</h2>
                <p>
                    If enabled in Settings (disabled by default), QuiKey may collect pseudonymous usage and diagnostic data (feature usage, success/failure rates, and error events) to help improve the app.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A pseudonymous device identifier is used to associate events from the same device.</li>
                    <li><strong>No file contents, email contents, or recipients are included</strong> in analytics events.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>To opt out: Go to Settings → General → Disable “Send usage metrics”.</p>

                <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>You have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> All data is stored locally on your Mac.</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete:</strong> You can clear history, logs, or "Reset to Defaults" in Settings.</li>
                    <li><strong>Revoke:</strong> Remove QuiKey from your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Account permissions</a> at any time.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>8. Contact</h2>
                <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:support@quikey.app">support@quikey.app</a></p>
                <p>See also: <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .privacy-page {
        padding: 120px 0 60px;
        min-height: 80vh;
    }

    .privacy-content {
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .privacy-content h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #1f2937;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .last-updated {
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #1f2937;
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #1f2937;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .privacy-content p {
        color: #4b5563;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-content ul {
        color: #4b5563;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-content a {
        color: #3b82f6;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .privacy-content a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .privacy-content strong {
        color: #1f2937;
    }

    .privacy-content code {
        background: #f3f4f6;
        padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-size: 0.9em;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .privacy-page {
            padding: 100px 0 40px;
        }

        .privacy-content h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }
    }
</style>
